reviews.text: They can’t speak English. The meat tastes very sweet and oily noodle so I disliked it. They’re not friendly. Unless you know how to speak Chinese, I feel like Hong Kong restaurants are not easy to tryout. Because most of them don’t know how to speak English.
Great food! Joeie’s service is the best and beyond my expectations.
All the menu ordered tasted fantastic. The place is nice and clean. Service is above Hong Kong average

75 mins of waiting. At which point we were so hungry it may have highten our taste buds. Food is 100% better than the one in Melbourne. Food was cooked very well. Worth 75mins waiting, maybe not. But if you don't have to wait it is worth a try.

Went mid week for dinner. Xlb was good, but not life changing for a Michelin star restaurant. We also had a dessert that was like a azuki bean filled beignet, but was a little soggy and overly sugary. 

Could have been when I went, but this place wouldn’t be my first choice of restaurant for the price/wait.

result.name: Crystal Jade

reviews.text: They have colourful 小籠包！ The taste is interesting and refreshing. Not sure if it’s something super cool for locals. It’s a photogenic and fun for foreigners I think.
Nice place, quick service. Love the soup dumplings

This Crystal Jade outlet attracted especially low rating comparing with its peers around HK. The reason seemed to be the poor services. To me, I did not feel the service here is any worse than the others though I did not expect much service for the whole chain of Crystal Jade. For the foods, I think they keep the standards of the group but for the price they charge this would be the minimum and they can do better. You can get better quality and tastier dishes and noodles elsewhere at lower prices. I'd say the premium you pay here is for the ambience, hygene, decoration and brandname.
Great food awesome dumplings and spicy noodles
The xiao long bao of the multi flavor set are surprisingly delicious!

reviews.text: Good shopping mall with a slightly upscale tint to it. Has nice open areas throughout and several floors to explore. Additionally, it does have several styles of cuisine and snacks on location, which makes it very good for just casual hanging out if you're in Tsuen Wan.
Shopping mall with a good variety of shops and restaurants, playground area good for kids.
Shop and restuarant are so great but car parking is poor

medium sized shopping centre but there are a number of this type of shopping centres that are connected by flyovers here. hence, it is a part of a huge shopping complex in the area. recommended if you would like to spend an afternoon here. you never run out of shopping options.
